history.content:
Hi there, 

Please see the pinned post about resolving course conflicts. It sounds like you maybe waited until the adjustment period to add this course? In future, if you need something for graduation, you need to phase 1 it.

I'm trying to enroll in CS 61C and there are a few open reserved spots left in the course (I'm declared). However, the open discussion sections conflict with my current schedule, which means that I must pick a waitlisted discussion section and can't enroll in the class. I have heard that I can attend any discussion I want and it sucks that this is what is blocking me from enrolling (I am now automatically waitlisted at position 103). I'm scared that by the time I can get the conflict form back the reserved spots will be full, leaving me on the waitlist for good. Is there anything I can do at this point? If I can't get 61C or 170 it's really going to set me back in terms of graduation.
